<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-07T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60F8/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-07T15:00:00+01:00">June 7, 1937—3
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 7—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>31. Your No. 10, April 13, 1 p.m. Practice of issuance of
                                certificates based upon local legislation. Foreign Office states
                                that situation is being studied by Council of Ministers and that
                                means are being sought to meet Treasury representation by
                                Ministerial decree with consideration to application of law to other
                                countries. Hope is expressed that Treasury will not make declaration
                                of bounty pending study here which I am assured will be
                                expedited.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>